The paper focuses on deep neural networks and their learning algorithms, which are primarily studied in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Random Matrix Theory to analyze the error function of the neural network suggests a focus on the mathematical and theoretical aspects of the problem, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with weight initialization, which is a common problem in neural networks and could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
